        h2.bs-docs-heading Small Screen Grids
        p
          | There are 2 different options for grids below the 768 breakpoint:&nbsp;
          strong Mobile-Grid
          | &nbsp;and&nbsp;
          strong No-Grid
          | . The small-screen grid will override the&nbsp;
          code
            | .grid
          | ,&nbsp;
          code
            | .slimgrid
          | &nbsp;or&nbsp;
          code
            | .slimgrid5
          | &nbsp;classes, and should be used in addition to them.

        h4.bs-docs-heading(style='padding-top:20px;') Mobile-Grid
        p
          | The mobile-grid utilizes&nbsp;
          strong 6 fluid columns
          | . To implement, add the appropriate m-grid class&nbsp;
          strong in addition&nbsp;
          | to your primary&nbsp;
          code
            | .grid
          | &nbsp;class. Class options are&nbsp;
          code
            | .m-grid-at-767
          | ,&nbsp;
          code
            | .m-grid-at-567
          | ,&nbsp;
          code
            | .m-grid-at-479
          | &nbsp;or&nbsp;
          code
            | .m-grid
          | &nbsp;(same as&nbsp;
          code
            | .m-grid-at-767
          | &nbsp;);
          | &nbsp;and add the appropriate&nbsp;
          code
            | .m-span
          | &nbsp;and (optionally)&nbsp;
          code
            | .m-offset
          | &nbsp;class to each column - again, in addition to the primary&nbsp;
          code
            | .span
          | &nbsp;class. The total mobile spans/offsets need to add up to 6.
        p.p4
          | Resize your browser to below 768px wide to see the mobile grid take effect.
          br
          | Hover over any of the columns to see the actual class names that affect it.
        div.grid.m-grid-at-767.show-grid
          div.span4.m-span1
            | 4 m1
          div.span4.m-span2
            | 4 m2
          div.span4.m-span2.m-offset1
            | 4 m2/1
        div.grid
          pre.prettyprint.prettyprint-jade
            | .grid.m-grid-at-767
            |   .span4.m-span1
            |   .span4.m-span2
            |   .span4.m-span2.m-offset1
        h4.bs-docs-heading No-Grid
        p
          | The
          strong &nbsp;no-grid&nbsp;
          | option collapses all grid spans into stacked rows, ignoring all&nbsp;
          code
            | .span
          | s,&nbsp;
          code
            | .offset
          | s,&nbsp;
          code
            | .m-span
          | s and&nbsp;
          code
            | .m-offset
          | s. To implement, add the appropriate no-grid class&nbsp;
          strong in addition
          | &nbsp;to your primary&nbsp;
          code
            | .grid
          | &nbsp;class. The classes available are&nbsp;
          code
            | .no-grid-at-767
          | ,&nbsp;
          code
            | .no-grid-at-567
          | , and&nbsp;
          code
            | .no-grid-at-479
          | .
